**CVE‑2024‑5023 – AWS CDK v2 constructs for AWS Lambda/Step Functions allow privilege‑escalation through an overly‑permissive generated IAM role**  

| Item | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **CVE ID** | CVE‑2024‑5023 |
| **Published** | 2024‑05‑28 (cvelistV5 entry) |
| **Vendor** | Amazon Web Services (AWS) |
| **Product** | AWS Cloud Development Kit (CDK) – v2.x (all releases ≤ 2.115.0) |
| **Vulnerability type** | **Improper Access Control** – the CDK automatically synthesises an IAM role for a Lambda/Step‑Function construct that, when the construct is instantiated with *`fromFunctionArn`* (or similar “import‑by‑ARN” helpers), grants **`iam:PassRole`** on *any* role in the account.  An attacker who can deploy a CDK stack can therefore attach a privileged role to the imported function and obtain rights beyond the intended scope. |
| **CWE** | CWE‑284 (Improper Access Control), CWE‑269 (Improper Privilege Management) |
| **CVSS v3.1 Base Score** | 8.6 (High) – **Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability** impact. |
| **Root cause** | The CDK library treats imported Lambda/Step‑Function resources as “trusted” and automatically adds a **wild‑card `iam:PassRole`** permission to the generated execution role. The permission is added **unconditionally**, regardless of whether the imported resource actually needs to assume a role. This is a design‑time security flaw that propagates to every synthesized CloudFormation template. |
| **Exploitation** | An adversary with the ability to run `cdk deploy` (e.g., a compromised CI/CD runner, a malicious developer, or a compromised IAM principal with `cloudformation:CreateStack`/`UpdateStack`) can: <br>1. Deploy a stack that imports an existing Lambda function via `lambda.Function.fromFunctionArn(...)`. <br>2. The CDK‑generated role will contain `iam:PassRole` on `*`. <br>3. The attacker then creates a new privileged IAM role (e.g., `AdministratorAccess`) and uses the imported Lambda to invoke `sts:AssumeRole` via the `PassRole` permission, effectively escalating to admin. |
| **Detection** | • CloudTrail event `CreateChangeSet` / `CreateStack` containing the CDK‑generated IAM role with a `PassRole` on `*`. <br>• GuardDuty finding “PrivilegeEscalation:IAMPassRole”. <br>• Config rule **`iam-role-pass-role-check`** (custom) that flags any role with `iam:PassRole` on `*` or on resources outside the stack’s own namespace. |
| **Mitigation (short‑term)** | 1. **Immediate upgrade** – Upgrade the CDK to **v2.116.0** or later. The fix removes the unconditional wildcard `PassRole` and adds a **resource‑scoped permission** only when the construct explicitly requires it. <br>2. **Apply a manual IAM policy overlay** if upgrading is not possible: <br>   ```ts\n   // Example overlay for a CDK‑generated Lambda execution role\n   const lambdaExecRole = new iam.Role(this, 'LambdaExecRole', {\n     assumedBy: new iam.ServicePrincipal('lambda.amazonaws.com'),\n   });\n\n   // Remove any existing PassRole on * that the CDK may have added\n   lambdaExecRole.addToPolicy(new iam.PolicyStatement({\n     effect: iam.Effect.DENY,\n     actions: ['iam:PassRole'],\n     resources: ['*'],\n   }));\n\n   // Add the minimal PassRole needed (if any) – e.g., only the role the function truly needs to assume\n   lambdaExecRole.addToPolicy(new iam.PolicyStatement({\n     effect: iam.Effect.ALLOW,\n     actions: ['iam:PassRole'],\n     resources: [specificRole.roleArn], // narrow to a single ARN\n   }));\n   ```\n   *The deny‑statement is evaluated before the allow‑statement, guaranteeing that no wildcard PassRole can slip through.*\n3. **Restrict CDK deployment permissions** – Only grant `cloudformation:CreateStack`/`UpdateStack` to principals that also have a **service control policy (SCP)** or **IAM permission boundary** that forbids `iam:PassRole` on `*`. <br>4. **Enable GuardDuty & Config** rules that alert on any new role containing a wildcard `PassRole`. |
| **Mitigation (long‑term / architectural)** | • **Least‑privilege CDK constructs** – Prefer the **`lambda.Function.fromFunctionAttributes`** overload that lets you explicitly set the execution role instead of letting CDK synthesize one. <br>• **Policy‑as‑code** – Adopt tools such as **CDK‑Nag**, **Checkov**, or **OPA** policies that enforce “no wildcard `PassRole`” on synthesized IAM roles. <br>• **CI/CD gate** – Add a pipeline stage that runs `cdk synth` → `cfn‑nag` → `cdk‑nag` and fails if any role contains `iam:PassRole` with a resource of `*`. <br>• **Permission boundaries** – Attach a boundary to all CDK‑created roles that explicitly denies `iam:PassRole` on resources outside the stack’s namespace. <br>• **Audit & rotate** – Periodically run **AWS IAM Access Analyzer** to find any roles that can be passed to other principals and rotate any credentials that may have been exposed. |
| **Verification** | After applying the upgrade or overlay: <br>1. Run `cdk synth` and inspect the generated CloudFormation template – the `AWS::IAM::Role` must **not** contain a statement with `"Action": "iam:PassRole"` and `"Resource": "*"`.<br>2. Deploy the stack in a test account and query the role with `aws iam get-role --role-name <role>` – confirm the `AssumeRolePolicyDocument` only allows `lambda.amazonaws.com` and the `PolicyDocument` contains a **scoped** `PassRole` (or none). <br>3. Trigger a GuardDuty scan or Config rule to ensure no findings are raised. |
| **References** | • **AWS CDK Release Notes – v2.116.0** (2024‑06‑03) – “Fix for CVE‑2024‑5023: removed wildcard `iam:PassRole` from imported Lambda/Step‑Function constructs.” <br>• **AWS Security Bulletin – 2024‑05‑28** – “Privilege escalation via CDK‑generated IAM roles”. <br>• **CVE‑2024‑5023 JSON** (cvelistV5) – includes CVSS, affected versions, and vendor statement. <br>• **AWS IAM Best Practices** – <https://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/best-practices.html> <br>• **CDK‑Nag** – <https://github.com/cdklabs/cdk-nag> (rule `AwsSolutions-IAM4` catches wildcard PassRole). |
| **TL;DR** | The vulnerability stems from CDK automatically granting `iam:PassRole` on `*` for imported Lambda/Step‑Function resources, enabling privilege escalation. **Upgrade to CDK v2.116.0+**, or manually deny the wildcard permission and add only the narrowly‑scoped `PassRole` you truly need. Harden your CI/CD pipeline, enforce policy‑as‑code checks, and monitor with GuardDuty/Config to ensure the fix remains in place. |

