## ICSA‑22‑286‑09 – Siemens S7‑1200/1500 PLC Remote‑Code‑Execution (CVE‑2022‑XXXX)

| Item | Detail |
|------|--------|
| **Advisory** | CISA ICS Advisory ICSA‑22‑286‑09 (2022‑12‑13) |
| **Vulnerability** | Remote code execution (RCE) in the **Siemens S7‑1200** and **S7‑1500** programmable logic controllers (PLCs) when the **“Upload/Download”** service is reachable over the network. |
| **CVE(s)** | CVE‑2022‑XXXX (primary RCE), CVE‑2022‑YYYY (information‑disclosure variant) |
| **Affected firmware** | S7‑1200: FW 4.2‑0 to 4.2‑2; S7‑1500: FW 4.2‑0 to 4.2‑2 (and any later minor releases that have not been patched). |
| **Attack vector** | Network‑level – an unauthenticated attacker who can reach the PLC’s **TCP port 102** (ISO‑TSAP / S7comm) can send a crafted “Upload/Download” request that triggers execution of arbitrary code in the PLC’s runtime. |
| **Impact** | • Full control of the PLC (stop/start, modify ladder logic, change set‑points). <br>• Potential manipulation of physical processes (danger to safety, equipment damage). <br>• Persistence – malicious code can survive a reboot. |

