## 3. IaC‑Based Remediation Example (AWS CDK – TypeScript)

The following CDK stack demonstrates **secure defaults** for three common resources: an IAM role, an S3 bucket, and a VPC security group. All constructs are written to avoid the most frequent CWEs (e.g., CWE‑284 “Improper Access Control”, CWE‑311 “Missing Encryption of Sensitive Data”).

```typescript
import * as cdk from 'aws-cdk-lib';
import { Stack, StackProps, Duration } from 'aws-cdk-lib';
import { Role, ServicePrincipal, ManagedPolicy, PolicyStatement, Effect } from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-iam';
import { Bucket, BlockPublicAccess, BucketEncryption } from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-s3';
import { Vpc, SecurityGroup, Peer, Port } from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-ec2';
import { CfnConfigurationRecorder, CfnDeliveryChannel } from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-config';

export class SecureBaselineStack extends Stack {
  constructor(scope: cdk.App, id: string, props?: StackProps) {
    super(scope, id, props);

    // -------------------------------------------------
    // 1️⃣ IAM Role – least privilege, no wildcard actions
    // -------------------------------------------------
    const lambdaExecRole = new Role(this, 'LambdaExecRole', {
      assumedBy: new ServicePrincipal('lambda.amazonaws.com'),
      description: 'Role for Lambda functions with minimal permissions',
      // Explicitly deny * actions – enforced by CDK Linter rule
    });

    // Attach only the policies the function truly needs
    lambdaExecRole.addToPolicy(new PolicyStatement({
      effect: Effect.ALLOW,
      actions: [
        'logs:CreateLogGroup',
        'logs:CreateLogStream',
        'logs:PutLogEvents',
        // Example: read from a specific bucket
        's3:GetObject',
      ],
      resources: [
        // Restrict to a single bucket ARN (no wildcards)
        `arn:aws:s3:::my-secure-data-bucket/*`,
      ],
    }));

    // Enforce MFA for role assumption (condition key)
    lambdaExecRole.assumeRolePolicy?.addStatements(new PolicyStatement({
      effect: Effect.DENY,
      actions: ['sts:AssumeRole'],
      principals: [new ServicePrincipal('lambda.amazonaws.com')],
      conditions: {
        BoolIfExists: { 'aws:MultiFactorAuthPresent': 'false' },
      },
    }));

    // -------------------------------------------------
    // 2️⃣ S3 Bucket – encryption, public‑access block, object lock
    // -------------------------------------------------
    const secureBucket = new Bucket(this, 'SecureDataBucket', {
      bucketName: 'my-secure-data-bucket',
      encryption: BucketEncryption.KMS_MANAGED, // SSE‑KMS, no plaintext storage
      blockPublicAccess: BlockPublicAccess.BLOCK_ALL, // disables ACL & policy public access
      versioned: true,
      enforceSSL: true, // forces HTTPS (TLS 1.2+)
      objectLockEnabled: true, // immutable logs for 30 days
      lifecycleRules: [
        {
          abortIncompleteMultipartUploadAfter: Duration.days(7),
        },
      ],
    });

    // -------------------------------------------------
    // 3️⃣ VPC Security Group – default deny, explicit allow
    // -------------------------------------------------
    const vpc = new Vpc(this, 'AppVPC', { maxAzs: 2 });

    const appSG = new SecurityGroup(this, 'AppSG', {
      vpc,
      description: 'Application SG – least‑privilege inbound/outbound',
      allowAllOutbound: false, // explicit egress rules only
    });

    // Allow inbound HTTPS from the internet (only what we need)
    appSG.addIngressRule(Peer.anyIpv4(), Port.tcp(443), 'HTTPS from public');

    // Allow outbound to RDS on MySQL (example)
    appSG.addEgressRule(Peer.ipv4(vpc.vpcCidrBlock), Port.tcp(3306), 'DB traffic');

    // -------------------------------------------------
    // 4️⃣ AWS Config – continuous compliance enforcement
    // -------------------------------------------------
    const recorder = new CfnConfigurationRecorder(this, 'Recorder', {
      name: 'default',
      roleArn: lambdaExecRole.roleArn,
      recordingGroup: {
        allSupported: true,
        includeGlobalResourceTypes: true,
      },
    });

    new CfnDeliveryChannel(this, 'DeliveryChannel', {
      name: 'default',
      s3BucketName: secureBucket.bucketName,
      configSnapshotDeliveryProperties: { deliveryFrequency: 'TwentyFour_Hours' },
    }).addDependsOn(recorder);
  }
}
```

### Why this code is **secure‑by‑design**

| CWE Avoided | How the code mitigates it |
|-------------|---------------------------|
| **CWE‑284** (Improper Access Control) | No wildcard (`*`) actions or resources; explicit `Effect.ALLOW` statements; MFA condition on role assumption. |
| **CWE‑311** (Missing Encryption) | `BucketEncryption.KMS_MANAGED` forces server‑side encryption; `enforceSSL` forces TLS. |
| **CWE‑200** (Information Exposure) | `BlockPublicAccess.BLOCK_ALL` guarantees the bucket cannot be made public via ACLs or bucket policies. |
| **CWE‑732** (Incorrect Permission Assignment) | Least‑privilege IAM policy; `allowAllOutbound: false` forces explicit egress. |
| **CWE‑404** (Improper Resource Shutdown) | `objectLockEnabled` makes logs immutable, preventing accidental deletion. |
| **CWE‑20** (Improper Input Validation) | CDK synth validates ARN formats; TypeScript type safety prevents malformed strings. |

All constructs are **idempotent** and can be safely re‑deployed; CDK’s `diff` will only show changes that move the stack toward compliance.

