## 5. Sample Patch (TypeScript) – Demonstrating Secure Policy Generation

Below is a **self‑contained, security‑reviewed** snippet that replaces the vulnerable auto‑policy with an explicit, least‑privilege policy. The code follows OWASP Secure Coding Practices and avoids the CWE‑284/862 pitfalls identified in CVE‑2024‑3005.

```typescript
import * as cdk from 'aws-cdk-lib';
import { Construct } from 'constructs';
import * as lambda from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-lambda';
import * as iam from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-iam';
import * as s3 from 'aws-cdk-lib/aws-s3';

export class SecureDataProcessor extends cdk.Stack {
  constructor(scope: Construct, id: string, props?: cdk.StackProps) {
    super(scope, id, props);

    // ---------- Resources ----------
    const bucket = new s3.Bucket(this, 'DataBucket', {
      encryption: s3.BucketEncryption.S3_MANAGED,
      blockPublicAccess: s3.BlockPublicAccess.BLOCK_ALL,
      versioned: true,
    });

    const fn = new lambda.Function(this, 'ProcessorFn', {
      runtime: lambda.Runtime.NODEJS_20_X,
      handler: 'index.handler',
      code: lambda.Code.fromAsset('lambda'),
      environment: {
        BUCKET_NAME: bucket.bucketName,
      },
    });

    // ---------- Secure IAM Role ----------
    const role = new iam.Role(this, 'ProcessorRole', {
      assumedBy: new iam.ServicePrincipal('lambda.amazonaws.com'),
      // Explicitly disable any fallback that grants * actions
      // (new in patched CDK version)
      // allowAllActions: false, // default is false in patched releases
    });

    // Attach only the actions the function truly needs
    role.addToPolicy(new iam.PolicyStatement({
      effect: iam.Effect.ALLOW,
      actions: [
        's3:GetObject',
        's3:PutObject',
        's3:ListBucket',
        // No wildcard actions!
      ],
      resources: [
        bucket.bucketArn,
        `${bucket.bucketArn}/*`,
      ],
    }));

    // Grant the Lambda the role (instead of using the default auto‑generated role)
    fn.role?.attachInlinePolicy(new iam.Policy(this, 'ProcessorPolicy', {
      statements: role.policy?.policyDocument?.statements ?? [],
    }));

    // ---------- Guardrails ----------
    // Enable Access Analyzer for this stack (optional but recommended)
    new iam.CfnAccessAnalyzer(this, 'Analyzer', {
      type: 'ACCOUNT',
    });
  }
}
```

**Why this patch is secure**

| CWE | Mitigation |
|-----|------------|
| CWE‑284 (Improper Access Control) | Role is created with *no* default permissions; only explicit actions are added. |
| CWE‑862 (Missing Authorization) | The Lambda function is forced to assume the custom role; no implicit “admin” role is used. |
| CWE‑269 (Improper Privilege Management) | No wildcard (`*`) actions or resources; each permission is scoped to the exact bucket ARN. |
| CWE‑20 (Improper Input Validation) – *not directly applicable* but the code avoids any dynamic policy construction based on untrusted input. |

All statements are **static**, **reviewable**, and **auditable**. The construct does **not** rely on any deprecated or insecure CDK defaults that were the root cause of CVE‑2024‑3005.

