*(MITRE ATT&CK® Enterprise – https://attack.mitre.org/mitigations/M0815)*  

---

## 1. What the mitigation addresses  

| ATT&CK Tactic | ATT&CK Technique(s) mitigated | Core idea of M0815 |
|---------------|------------------------------|--------------------|
| **Execution**, **Privilege Escalation**, **Defense Evasion** | • T1059 – Command‑Line Interface  <br>• T1068 – Exploitation for Privilege Escalation  <br>• T1204 – User Execution  <br>• T1547 – Boot or Logon Autostart Execution | Reduce the likelihood that vulnerable or malicious code can be introduced into a cloud workload by enforcing *secure‑by‑design* development, rigorous testing, and continuous verification.  

The mitigation is **preventive** – it does **not** rely on detection after the fact but on eliminating the root cause (insecure code) that attackers exploit.

