## 6.  Defense‑in‑Depth Checklist (Least‑Privilege, Secure‑by‑Design)

| Layer | Recommended Controls |
|-------|----------------------|
| **Physical** | Locked PLC cabinets, tamper‑evident seals, CCTV coverage. |
| **Network** | • VLAN isolation (as above).<br>• ACLs that deny all inbound traffic except trusted HMI/SCADA IPs.<br>• Use MAC‑based port security on switches. |
| **Transport** | • Enable TLS 1.2+ on any PLC web services (if required).<br>• Deploy a TLS‑terminating reverse proxy that validates client certificates. |
| **Authentication** | • Disable default “admin” accounts.<br>• Enforce multi‑factor authentication for any remote access (VPN + IAM). |
| **Integrity** | • Verify firmware signatures before flashing.<br>• Enable Secure Boot on PLCs that support it. |
| **Audit** | • Centralize syslog to a write‑once log server.<br>• Enable “Change History” in TIA Portal and export daily. |
| **Incident Response** | • Pre‑define a playbook: isolate PLC → capture volatile memory (`dumpcfg`) → revert to known‑good firmware snapshot. |
| **Supply‑Chain** | • Only procure Siemens‑signed modules; maintain a hardware inventory with serial numbers. |

