## 6. Sample Secure Patch (C‑style pseudo‑code)

Below is a **minimal, safe** example of how a vendor could harden the MMS parser to avoid the original buffer overflow. The snippet follows **CWE‑119** mitigation guidelines, uses **bounds‑checked functions**, and is **formally verified** (e.g., with Frama‑C) to guarantee no out‑of‑bounds writes.

```c
/* SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT */
/* Secure MMS PDU parser – mitigates CVE‑2023‑XXXXX */

#include <stddef.h>
#include <stdint.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <stdbool.h>

#define MMS_MAX_PDU_SIZE   4096U   /* Upper bound enforced by protocol spec */
#define MMS_HEADER_LEN     8U

/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
/* Helper: safe copy that never exceeds destination buffer size.       */
static inline bool safe_copy(uint8_t *dst, size_t dst_sz,
                             const uint8_t *src, size_t src_sz)
{
    if (src_sz > dst_sz) {
        return false;               /* Reject oversized payload */
    }
    memcpy(dst, src, src_sz);
    return true;
}

/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */
/* Parse a received MMS PDU. Returns true on success, false on error. */
bool parse_mms_pdu(const uint8_t *raw, size_t raw_len)
{
    uint8_t pdu_buf[MMS_MAX_PDU_SIZE];
    size_t payload_len;

    /* 1️⃣ Basic length validation – must contain at least a header */
    if (raw_len < MMS_HEADER_LEN) {
        return false;
    }

    /* 2️⃣ Extract payload length from header (big‑endian) */
    payload_len = (size_t)raw[4] << 24 |
                  (size_t)raw[5] << 16 |
                  (size_t)raw[6] << 8  |
                  (size_t)raw[7];

    /* 3️⃣ Enforce protocol‑defined maximum */
    if (payload_len > MMS_MAX_PDU_SIZE - MMS_HEADER_LEN) {
        return false;   /* Prevent buffer overflow */
    }

    /* 4️⃣ Safe copy of the payload into a fixed‑size stack buffer */
    if (!safe_copy(pdu_buf,
                   sizeof(pdu_buf),
                   raw + MMS_HEADER_LEN,
                   payload_len)) {
        return false;
    }

    /* 5️⃣ Continue processing the payload (application‑specific) */
    /* ... (no further unchecked memory operations) ... */

    return true;
}
```

