| **Data‑Loss‑Prevention (DLP) & Content Inspection** | Detects large or sensitive payloads being written to public locations. | Enable **Amazon Macie** for S3, configure **AWS Config Rules** (`s3-bucket-public-read-prohibited`, `s3-bucket-ssl-requests-only`). |
| **Egress Filtering** | Blocks unauthorized outbound connections (e.g., to unknown SaaS endpoints). | Deploy **Network ACLs** and **Security Groups** that only allow traffic to approved IP ranges; use **AWS Network Firewall** with domain‑allowlist rules. |
| **Comprehensive Logging & Alerting** | Provides telemetry to detect anomalous exfiltration attempts. | Turn on **AWS CloudTrail (multi‑region, data‑events)**, **VPC Flow Logs**, **S3 Access Logs**, and forward to **Amazon CloudWatch Logs** for SIEM correlation. |
| **Automated Remediation** | Reduces dwell time once an exfiltration attempt is spotted. | Use **EventBridge** rules that trigger **AWS Lambda** to quarantine the offending IAM principal or revoke the bucket policy. |

