**MITRE ATT&CK – Technique T0817 – “Exploitation for Privilege Escalation (Cloud)”**  

| Aspect | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Goal of the adversary** | Leverage a vulnerability in a cloud‑native service, runtime component, or underlying infrastructure to obtain a higher‑privilege identity (e.g., root, admin, or a privileged IAM role). |
| **Typical vectors** | <ul><li>Unpatched managed services (e.g., RDS, Elasticsearch, Lambda runtime)</li><li>Vulnerable container images or base AMIs</li><li>Mis‑configured IAM policies that allow “privilege escalation” actions (e.g., `iam:PassRole`, `sts:AssumeRole` on privileged roles)</li><li>Exposed management APIs (e.g., EC2 Instance Metadata Service v1, S3 bucket policies that allow `PutObject` on privileged buckets)</li></ul> |
| **Observable telemetry** | <ul><li>AWS CloudTrail events: `AssumeRole`, `UpdateAssumeRolePolicy`, `CreateAccessKey`, `Put*` on privileged resources</li><li>GuardDuty findings: “PrivilegeEscalation:IAMUser/Role” or “PrivilegeEscalation:EC2Metadata”</li><li>Vulnerability scanner alerts (Amazon Inspector, Snyk, Trivy) reporting CVEs in managed services or container images</li><li>Unexpected changes in IAM policy versions or new inline policies attached to high‑privilege principals</li></ul> |

