| CWE‑798 (Hard‑coded credentials) | No secrets are embedded; configuration values are read from Secrets Manager or environment variables that are injected at runtime. |
| CWE‑269 (Improper privilege) | Execution role grants only `s3:GetObject` on a specific bucket. |
| CWE‑200 (Information exposure) | Logs are retained for a limited period and do not contain sensitive payloads. |
| CWE‑307 (Improper authentication) | Code signing is enforced, preventing unsigned or tampered code from being deployed. |
| CWE‑665 (Improper initialization) | The Lambda asset is immutable (`fromAsset`) and version‑controlled. |

