## MITRE ATT&CK Mitigation **M0951 – “Use Secure Development Practices”**  
*(also described as “Secure Development Lifecycle (SDL) / Secure Coding”)*  

| **What it addresses** | **Why it matters** |
|-----------------------|--------------------|
| Reduces the likelihood that malicious code, insecure configurations, or vulnerable third‑party components make it into production. | Attackers often exploit software bugs, insecure defaults, or mis‑configured cloud resources that were introduced during development or CI/CD. By embedding security checks early, the attack surface is dramatically shrunk. |

