## 1. Threat‑Model Context

| Asset | Threat | Attack Vector |
|-------|--------|---------------|
| PLC firmware | Remote code execution (RCE) | Crafted TCP packets to port 102 (or HTTP request to port 80/443) from any reachable network segment |
| Network | Lateral movement to other PLCs / HMIs | Unsegmented OT‑IT convergence zones, VPNs, or cloud‑based remote‑access gateways |
| Management interfaces (e.g., cloud‑based SCADA, AWS IoT SiteWise) | Credential theft / abuse | Over‑privileged IAM roles, permissive security‑group rules |

The advisory therefore calls for **defense‑in‑depth**: patch the firmware, isolate the PLCs, and harden any cloud‑native components that provide remote connectivity.

